02:51.100 --> 02:54.970
Your honor, mr. Betancourt
is our new general counsel.

02:55.520 --> 02:58.420
He's ably taken the
reins from ms. Maddox.

02:58.750 --> 03:02.120
Well, then I trust it, uh, won't
be necessary to delay this case.

03:02.150 --> 03:04.660
N-no, your honor, I am
entirely up to speed.

03:04.700 --> 03:09.860
And I see this motion as a matter of
ethical constraints, pure and simple.

03:09.890 --> 03:13.860
The only pure and simple thing about
this case is your client's malfeasance.

03:13.900 --> 03:16.660
Malfeasance? Really?

03:18.110 --> 03:24.650
Your honor, ms. Hewes is in violation of
the new york disciplinary rule 1-dash-102a,

03:24.660 --> 03:27.320
subsections three, four and five.

03:27.370 --> 03:28.830
You have no proof of that.

03:28.860 --> 03:33.630
The evidence ms. Hewes has proffered could
only have come from the suv in question,

03:33.640 --> 03:37.900
and the only way she could have
procured it is through criminal means.

03:38.490 --> 03:40.120
She stole the car.

03:40.160 --> 03:42.450
That is ludicrous.

03:42.460 --> 03:48.590
And I intend to present witnesses corroborating
unr's involvement in fraudulent commodities trading.

03:48.600 --> 03:50.490
Forget about your witnesses.

03:50.530 --> 03:55.810
Would you have this corroboration without the
information extracted illegally from the vehicle?

03:55.840 --> 03:58.240
All right, enough.
I'll read your briefs.

03:58.700 --> 04:01.170
Then I'll let you know...

04:01.180 --> 04:05.300
whether this, uh, suv
evidence is admissible.

04:05.570 --> 04:08.720
You'll hear from me again
after I've made my ruling.

04:08.730 --> 04:10.970
- Thank you, your honor.
- Thank you.

04:11.840 --> 04:13.650
Ms.Hewes?

04:14.950 --> 04:17.709
Based on what I've heard so far...

04:18.130 --> 04:20.630
I'm inclined to side with the defense.

04:20.640 --> 04:23.350
I understand, your honor.

04:30.960 --> 04:34.360
Patty? You wanted to see me?

04:35.340 --> 04:38.240
The judge needs these
to make his ruling.

04:38.250 --> 04:40.680
I want you to file this.

04:40.690 --> 04:43.220
- What is it?
- The gps codes.

04:43.230 --> 04:45.090
They'll be inadmissible.

04:45.120 --> 04:46.550
Just do it.

04:46.560 --> 04:49.230
Have you made arrangements
with judge oliver?

04:51.540 --> 04:54.430
Why did you fire tom?

04:54.880 --> 04:57.440
I'd prefer not to talk about that.

04:57.450 --> 05:00.730
He wouldn't go through
with it, would he?

05:05.550 --> 05:07.500
Let me do this for you.

05:07.510 --> 05:10.250
I told you, I don't want you involved.

05:10.270 --> 05:12.870
You're being investigated--
you can't do it yourself.

05:12.920 --> 05:14.730
Who says I'm gonna do it at all?

05:14.760 --> 05:16.110
What is the alternative?

05:16.160 --> 05:20.880
The alternative... is to believe
in our case and trust the system.

05:20.890 --> 05:23.150
Judge oliver doesn't
believe in the system.

05:23.180 --> 05:25.400
He believes in money.

05:31.850 --> 05:34.210
All right, ellen.

05:36.570 --> 05:39.350
Find out what his terms are.

05:49.830 --> 05:51.810
Did you do it?

05:53.200 --> 05:55.400
Ellen parsons...

05:55.440 --> 05:57.610
is alive and well.

05:58.980 --> 06:01.000
That's disappointing.

06:01.020 --> 06:03.250
Not gonna do it.

06:04.720 --> 06:07.360
You just made a big decision.

06:09.860 --> 06:12.510
I don't care what you do to me.

06:13.840 --> 06:15.570
I'm out.

06:16.200 --> 06:18.720
And good luck finding me.

06:25.840 --> 06:28.680
Thanks for coming.

06:29.250 --> 06:30.850
How's the baby?

06:30.880 --> 06:33.060
What do you want?

06:33.760 --> 06:36.780
I'm sorry... it had to be like this.

06:36.790 --> 06:39.080
- Are you?
- Yes.

06:39.970 --> 06:42.820
But you're better off this way.

06:42.850 --> 06:46.830
Oh, your ego is astonishing.

06:47.340 --> 06:49.730
Patty is going to jail, tom.

06:49.760 --> 06:53.190
The more distance you get from
her, the better off you are.

06:53.750 --> 06:58.730
I'll never be able to figure it out.In less
than six months you're in her inner circle,

06:58.740 --> 07:03.270
god knows why, and all you
had to do was stay loyal.

07:03.670 --> 07:06.590
- Oh, you think this is about loyalty?
- Look...

07:07.140 --> 07:12.010
patty is-is... is no saint--
she crosses the line sometimes.

07:12.020 --> 07:16.790
But she does it for a reason-- she fights for
people that nobody else gives a shit about.

07:18.200 --> 07:21.470
Why are you doing this to her?
What did she ever do to you?

07:34.980 --> 07:37.650
Don't do anything stupid, tom.

07:37.660 --> 07:41.790
You tip patty off, the feds can still
use everything they have against you.

08:50.170 --> 08:52.600
Wes, is that you?

08:59.910 --> 09:01.040
Wes?

09:01.050 --> 09:04.150
Yeah, it's me.

09:11.870 --> 09:14.200
You know, there's a
warrant out for your arrest.

09:14.230 --> 09:16.310
You stay away from her.

09:16.320 --> 09:20.780
The next time I see you,
there won't be a conversation.

09:23.140 --> 09:25.060
now leave.

09:25.070 --> 09:28.020
You can't proct her everywhere.

09:36.240 --> 09:39.200
So...

09:44.620 --> 09:46.850
you really did it?

09:48.930 --> 09:51.240
Yes.

09:58.730 --> 10:03.210
I know you can't help me with
aracite, but I still need you, daniel.

10:04.780 --> 10:08.650
You know how unr
conducted their business.

10:08.660 --> 10:11.670
You were privy to their fraud.

10:11.690 --> 10:14.670
You can still help
me to bring them down.

10:15.180 --> 10:18.290
You want the testimony of a murderer?

10:18.530 --> 10:22.890
Even if you killed christine,
they helped you cover it up.

10:24.010 --> 10:26.580
You'll never understand.

10:26.620 --> 10:29.000
Understand what?

10:29.020 --> 10:31.760
To find peace...

10:33.410 --> 10:37.400
I have to take full
responsibility for my sins.

10:40.520 --> 10:43.640
Forget your work, patty.

10:44.570 --> 10:47.700
Pay attention to your life.

10:49.740 --> 10:53.250
Your family. I mean,
it's too late for me.

10:57.960 --> 11:02.050
but there will be no more
betrayals, no more lies.

11:08.000 --> 11:11.520
I want my daughter to know...

11:12.510 --> 11:15.320
who I am.

11:19.640 --> 11:23.040
It must feel like you're
looking in a mirror.

11:23.050 --> 11:27.160
But there's a difference
between you and me.

11:27.830 --> 11:30.630
I've confessed.

11:36.310 --> 11:38.500
I got to go.

11:39.250 --> 11:41.880
Patty, wait.

11:47.580 --> 11:50.540
Tell michael...

11:52.970 --> 11:56.400
he doesn't have to be like us.

12:15.070 --> 12:20.190
This, uh, this gift
isn't for my personal use.

12:20.240 --> 12:23.700
It would be going straight
into my reelection campaign.

12:23.750 --> 12:27.060
We need to ensure the right
kind of judges stay on the bench.

12:27.070 --> 12:29.090
I agree.

12:32.840 --> 12:36.190
Looks like you've really
earned patty's trust.

12:37.640 --> 12:40.420
She knows that i believe
in what she's doing.

12:41.270 --> 12:44.910
Tell patty she can
contribute the usual amount.

12:45.640 --> 12:49.450
Thank you, your honor. I'll
let you know what she decides.

12:57.910 --> 13:00.220
How did it go with purcell?

13:01.960 --> 13:03.440
He won't be useful.

13:03.450 --> 13:06.580
Well, judge oliver's ready.

13:07.030 --> 13:08.470
What are his terms?

13:08.520 --> 13:11.140
He said "the usual."

13:13.400 --> 13:16.220
Should I tell him we're good?

13:18.360 --> 13:21.070
I don't know.

13:21.080 --> 13:23.690
There's something about it.

13:26.030 --> 13:28.350
Don't you think?

13:28.360 --> 13:31.140
What other choice do we have?

13:31.170 --> 13:33.350
We're out of options.

13:33.360 --> 13:36.660
There's no other way
to prove those trades.

13:38.360 --> 13:41.140
There's still one long shot.

13:54.000 --> 13:55.090
Yeah?

13:55.130 --> 13:56.960
- Mr. Garrety?
- Who are you?

13:56.970 --> 13:59.390
My name is patty hewes. I'm an attorney.

13:59.400 --> 14:02.510
- I'm not interested.
- I think you're going to want to talk to me.

14:02.520 --> 14:04.030
About what?

14:04.040 --> 14:07.670
The illegal energy trades
you made for walter kendrick.

14:07.680 --> 14:09.350
Never heard of him.

14:09.390 --> 14:11.950
Then let's talk about dave pell.

14:12.940 --> 14:16.360
I have a list of the stock
trades you made for mr. Pell.

14:16.610 --> 14:20.200
A man's wife was murdered
to protect your investments.

14:20.230 --> 14:24.740
And the company you've been trading has poisoned
thousands of people so you could turn your profits.

14:24.800 --> 14:26.450
I don't know anything about that.

14:26.490 --> 14:29.130
Maybe not. Anyway, I
don't care, mr. Garrety.

14:29.400 --> 14:32.380
I've been having one hell of a shitty
month, and someone is gonna pay.

14:32.420 --> 14:33.460
What do you want from me?

14:33.510 --> 14:38.020
I need you to corroborate how you used
gps coordinates to make your stock trades.

14:38.050 --> 14:39.780
I need you to testify.

14:39.820 --> 14:42.060
Why the hell would i do that?

14:42.100 --> 14:44.820
Because you're in
business with my enemies.

14:44.860 --> 14:47.190
And that's the last stupid
mistake you're gonna make.

14:47.240 --> 14:49.660
Listen, lady, you're lucky
I don't crack you in the jaw.

14:49.720 --> 14:52.810
Just ask around, mr. Garrety.

14:52.830 --> 14:57.660
Find out who I am, and then decide whose
side you want to be on-- theirs or mine.

14:57.670 --> 15:00.120
- Leave.
- Once.

15:00.820 --> 15:03.460
I'll make this offer once.

15:03.470 --> 15:08.150
You close this door, it
will never open again.

15:08.480 --> 15:11.690
Help me or you're going to
jail with the rest of them.

15:13.850 --> 15:16.550
I'll take my chances.

15:21.400 --> 15:23.870
Your choice.

15:33.370 --> 15:35.570
- Ms.Parsons.
- Yes?

15:36.790 --> 15:39.750
I'm detective rick messer, nypd.

15:40.720 --> 15:42.830
You look familiar.

15:42.840 --> 15:44.880
We met once before.

15:44.930 --> 15:47.920
I was working a string
of homicides downtown.

15:47.940 --> 15:50.570
Your fianc? s murder fit the profile.

15:51.960 --> 15:54.900
This is detective rick messer. He
asked if he could take a look around.

15:54.910 --> 15:58.990
I'm very sorry for your loss.
I hope they find the guy.

16:00.700 --> 16:02.900
Can we speak someplace private?

16:03.960 --> 16:06.560
Sure.

16:07.040 --> 16:09.330
His name is eliot tolken.

16:09.340 --> 16:12.490
He was a beat cop for
more than a decade.

16:12.500 --> 16:15.860
As you can see, his whereabouts
are currently unknown.

16:15.870 --> 16:19.350
But I have reason to believe he was involved
in the homicides i was investigating.

16:19.390 --> 16:21.740
And in the murder of my fianc?

16:21.780 --> 16:23.810
I want to help, ms. Parsons...

16:24.980 --> 16:27.310
but I'm not here in
an official capacity.

16:27.350 --> 16:28.790
Why are you here?

16:28.810 --> 16:32.090
Because if I'm right
and tolken was involved,

16:32.100 --> 16:36.690
then someone in my department may be
trying to stonewall my investigation.

16:37.970 --> 16:39.760
I see.

16:39.790 --> 16:41.810
I reopened your file.

16:41.850 --> 16:45.030
There is a partial print on the murder
weapon that was never identified.

16:45.060 --> 16:46.810
You think it's tolken's?

16:46.840 --> 16:49.360
I'm having it analyzed.

16:49.740 --> 16:53.500
I'm gonna solve this, ms. Parsons.

16:54.110 --> 16:57.390
But I suggest you keep this
conversation between us.

16:57.410 --> 17:02.300
Accusing a police officer of a crime
can be a very dangerous proposition.

17:03.260 --> 17:05.819
I understand.

17:10.310 --> 17:12.670
When the print comes
back, I'll be in touch.

17:12.680 --> 17:15.400
Thank you, detective.

17:22.390 --> 17:25.349
The detective who came
to see you is legit.

17:25.359 --> 17:27.400
How do you know?

17:27.410 --> 17:31.070
Rick messer has almost
20 years on the force,

17:31.080 --> 17:34.170
half a dozen commendations
and a sterling reputation.

17:34.200 --> 17:35.740
So we can trust him?

17:35.770 --> 17:39.600
Uh, I spoke to my contact
in the commissioner's office.

17:39.630 --> 17:41.900
Messer sounds like a stand-up guy.

17:41.910 --> 17:44.490
Good. He said he'd be in touch.

17:44.500 --> 17:47.300
This is what he had on officer tolken.

17:49.350 --> 17:51.960
You're sure this is the guy
that followed you on the street?

17:51.970 --> 17:52.930
Yes.

17:52.940 --> 17:55.010
- Can I hang onto this?
- Sure.

17:55.020 --> 17:57.780
We'll find out how this
guy connects to frobisher.

17:58.750 --> 18:00.660
I can't wait for you
to see this building.

18:00.700 --> 18:02.980
It's unbelievable, holly. They've got...

18:03.350 --> 18:06.490
they've got windmills on the roof. Yeah.

18:06.500 --> 18:08.400
Hey, ron, let me catch
up with you later.

18:08.430 --> 18:10.230
- I'm on the phone with
my ex-wife. - It's don.

18:10.240 --> 18:15.130
It's an environmentally responsible
leed-certified green building.

18:15.210 --> 18:18.100
Perfect headquarters for my new company.

18:18.650 --> 18:21.480
Yeah. Yeah, I know.

18:21.490 --> 18:25.350
Hey, I can't wait to
see you and the kids.

18:25.360 --> 18:29.350
I know-I know it's just a first
step, but I'm excited, babe.

18:29.390 --> 18:33.170
I-I tell you, the future's
looking bright again. Yeah!

18:34.450 --> 18:36.630
Hey, mom.

18:39.650 --> 18:42.050
I read your college essay.

18:42.060 --> 18:44.380
Oh, yeah? What did you think?

18:44.390 --> 18:46.930
- I was confused.
- Why?

18:46.940 --> 18:49.490
I told you I was writing
about daniel purcell.

18:49.500 --> 18:51.520
No.

18:51.560 --> 18:56.530
I was confused by the fact that all your
applications are still in your bedroom.

18:58.080 --> 18:59.880
Good. You went through my room.

18:59.890 --> 19:02.050
You never applied anywhere.

19:02.640 --> 19:04.110
Because I'm not going to college.

19:04.160 --> 19:06.090
Why not?

19:06.730 --> 19:09.480
For you, mom. Look at you.

19:10.290 --> 19:12.770
What is that supposed to mean?

19:12.790 --> 19:15.000
You need a man in your life.

19:15.020 --> 19:17.650
And you have no one left but me.

19:27.190 --> 19:28.910
Relax, walt.

19:28.930 --> 19:31.730
The judge won't be
ruling in patty's favor.

19:32.300 --> 19:34.260
I don't share your confidence.

19:34.300 --> 19:36.990
It doesn't matter anyway.
Patty's gonna bribe him.

19:37.740 --> 19:41.660
And when she does, the fbi
will be there to arrest her.

19:42.220 --> 19:44.340
How the hell do you know that?

19:44.400 --> 19:49.200
There's an informant in patty
hewes's firm working with the fbi.

19:52.110 --> 19:55.790
Goddamn, it's always a pleasure
doing business with you.

19:55.800 --> 19:59.090
There's a finn garrety
here to see you, mr. Pell.

19:59.100 --> 20:00.210
What does he want?

20:00.260 --> 20:03.730
I have no idea. Send him in.

20:08.150 --> 20:10.360
Did you kill a woman?

20:11.580 --> 20:14.460
Oh, look, it's the asshole who runs unr.

20:14.470 --> 20:16.150
You don't want to talk to me like that.

20:16.200 --> 20:18.750
Really? Aren't you the
guy poisoning people?

20:18.760 --> 20:20.520
That's enough, mr. Garrety.

20:20.550 --> 20:23.380
Patty hewes came to see me.

20:23.390 --> 20:27.840
Wanted my testimony about
the trades we've been making.

20:27.880 --> 20:28.730
What'd you tell her?

20:28.770 --> 20:31.740
I told her to go screw herself, for now.

20:31.780 --> 20:32.440
For now?

20:32.490 --> 20:37.400
You put me smack in the middle
of a big pile of shit, gentlemen.

20:37.430 --> 20:42.160
I agreed to take your
codes, make some trades.

20:43.250 --> 20:45.610
You never told me
anything else was going on.

20:45.650 --> 20:47.740
What exactly do you want, mr. Garrety?

20:47.770 --> 20:51.280
Let's start with a piece of the
company, a major ownership stake.

20:51.320 --> 20:53.710
- You're out of your mind.
- Goddamn right.

20:53.720 --> 20:58.180
I'm a frickin' madman,
crazy enough to talk.

20:59.060 --> 21:04.540
You got 24 hours, or I cut
a deal with patty hewes.

21:21.420 --> 21:25.660
And I enjoy the diet. Everybody
has problems with diets today.

21:25.670 --> 21:30.020
They get bored with them, and
most diets, people don't stay on.

21:30.050 --> 21:34.670
People buy this machine because it's easy
to clean, but the food tastes so good.

21:34.700 --> 21:38.580
Now, if you're on a diet-- chicken,
fish or beef-- high protein.

21:38.610 --> 21:41.070
Well, that's what this machine
does: Chicken, fish or beef.

21:41.100 --> 21:44.410
So you always look
forward to eating the food.

21:44.440 --> 21:49.230
And that, I believe, is gonna encourage people to
stay on the diet, and that's the important thing.

21:49.270 --> 21:52.500
Now, once you reach that weight--
I've reached the weight already.

21:52.560 --> 21:56.970
In fact, I'm trying to gain a pound.
Then you start to increase the carbs.

21:56.980 --> 21:59.790
We can start eating a little bit...

22:01.030 --> 22:02.360
What's all this?

22:02.410 --> 22:07.640
Stefania's been going through uncle
pete's things, and she sent these over.

22:09.470 --> 22:12.300
Looks like some nice memories.

22:16.570 --> 22:19.100
Is this you?

22:50.300 --> 22:52.340
who's that?

22:54.870 --> 22:58.560
No idea. Never seen him before.

23:09.160 --> 23:11.930
Patty may bribe a judge.

23:11.940 --> 23:14.880
Feds could have her in custody soon.

23:17.360 --> 23:20.010
Congratulations.

23:21.150 --> 23:24.020
What's wrong?

23:24.870 --> 23:27.810
